          <div class="col-lg-12 portfolio-info">
            <br>
            <h2 style="color:#12d640">eVTOL: Tiltrotor & Landing Gear</h2>

            <p><strong>Summary:</strong> Designed and fabricated the tiltrotor mechanism and landing gear for a ¼-scale eVTOL prototype. Leveraged SolidWorks and Fusion360 for CAD and analysis, integrating structural and aerodynamic constraints into a manufacturable design. System incorporated FAA-compliant load case validation and weight-optimized carbon-fiber structures for improved efficiency.</p>

            <h4>Requirements:</h4>
            <ul>
              <li>Support FAA-compliant load cases for tiltrotor and landing gear systems</li>
              <li>Validate structural integrity under worst-case loading scenarios</li>
              <li>Maintain low weight while ensuring safety margins</li>
              <li>Enhance overall flight efficiency through optimized design</li>
            </ul>

            <h4>Main Components:</h4>
            <ul>
              <li><strong>Tiltrotor Mechanism:</strong> Modeled and fabricated mechanism enabling variable rotor positioning for vertical and horizontal flight modes. Verified strength and deflection performance through FEA simulations.</li>
              <li><strong>Landing Gear:</strong> Developed robust carbon-fiber landing gear capable of absorbing impact loads during touchdown. Designed geometry to minimize weight while achieving ±15% mass reduction compared to baseline aluminum designs.</li>
            </ul>

            <h4>Key Outcomes:</h4>
            <ul>
              <li>Achieved FAA-compliant validation for structural performance</li>
              <li>Reduced mass of carbon-fiber components by 15%, improving endurance and efficiency</li>
              <li>Ensured safe, reliable operation for ¼-scale prototype under test conditions</li>
            </ul>

            <p><strong>Skills:</strong> CAD & FEA (SolidWorks, Fusion360), Carbon-Fiber Design, FAA Load Case Analysis, Materials Optimization, Prototyping & Manufacturing</p>

